review_text
"Something about evil twins strong hoppy beer that is punishingly sweet. I hated the single hop Molotov, and while this isn't quite so diabetic, it's majorly sweet, especially for a wheat lager. Not sure why, but it is. It really takes away from the mosaic hops, which smell a whole lot more alive and awesome than they taste. Goes great with the wheat malt, which is robust in both flavor and texture. Grainy but sort, with. Ice bubbles, if this were drier it would feel amazing. Nice combination of flavors, and well balanced, but so sweet as to be distracting, and not just in the finish but all the way through. Hard to tell its a lager, not much yeast flavor here and no crispness because of the sugar. I had it on tap, but have heard bottles are much better for some reason. Still love evil twin, but this had way more potential. Add Brett and give it a year I bet it would be epic!"
