"22oz bottle. Pours a semi translucent brownish orange with over an inch of thick white head. Lots of lacing. The aroma is citrus and floral hops. Tangerine, honey, lemon, flowers and some spicy wheat notes. The taste is honey and floral hops followed by some tangerine and orange peel. Hints of lermon and lime. Nice amount of wheat flavor with some tropical notes towards the end. Bready. Finishes with tangerines, wheat and honey. Super carbonated. Can't be in a hurry to drink this one. ""Mosaic"" is what caught my eye for this one. Overall, pretty interesting beer I'd buy again."
